    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "How long does an MRI ARM take?",
        "answer": "Routine scan: 20 minutes; high-resolution or contrast study: 30–35 minutes.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is the scan painful?",
        "answer": "No. You may feel slight warmth; no injections unless contrast is used.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I drive after the scan?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless you received sedation (rare). Most patients resume normal activities immediately.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will I get my report?",
        "answer": "Same-day soft copy by 8 p.m.; hard copy available next morning.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Do I need a doctor’s referral?",
        "answer": "Yes, for insurance claims. Walk-ins accepted for self-pay patients.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I'm claustrophobic and need an Arm MRI?  ",
        "answer": "If you suffer from claustrophobia, please inform the Cadabams Diagnostics staff and your doctor when scheduling your **Arm MRI**. Options may include listening to music through headphones, having a friend or family member present (if facility policy allows and they are also screened for safety), physician-prescribed medication for anxiety, or potentially using an open MRI scanner if available at Cadabams Diagnostics and suitable for the specific arm imaging required.  "
      },
      {
        "question": " What is the approximate cost of an Arm MRI scan?  ",
        "answer": "The **cost of an arm mri scan** can vary. Factors influencing the cost include whether contrast material is used, the complexity of the scan, your specific insurance coverage, and geographic location. For precise pricing information related to your Arm MRI at Cadabams Diagnostics, please contact our billing or patient admissions department directly."
      }
    ],
